412 template <typename T>
413 class WeakCallbackInfo {
414  public:
415  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
416 
417  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
418  void* internal_fields[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback],
419  Callback* callback)
420  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
421  for (int i = 0; i < kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
422  internal_fields_[i] = internal_fields[i];
423  }
424  }
425 
426  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
427  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
428  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
429 
430  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
431  void* GetInternalField1() const) {
432  return internal_fields_[0];
433  }
434  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
435  void* GetInternalField2() const) {
436  return internal_fields_[1];
437  }
438 
439  V8_DEPRECATED("Not realiable once SetSecondPassCallback() was used.",
440  bool IsFirstPass() const) {
441  return callback_ != nullptr;
442  }
443 
444  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
445  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
446  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
447  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
448  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
449  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
450  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
451 
452  private:
453  Isolate* isolate_;
454  T* parameter_;
455  Callback* callback_;
456  void* internal_fields_[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback];
457 };

575  // Phantom persistents work like weak persistents, except that the pointer to
576  // the object being collected is not available in the finalization callback.
577  // This enables the garbage collector to collect the object and any objects

579  // specify a parameter for the callback or the location of two internal
580  // fields in the dying object.

1169 
1170  // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1171  // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1172  // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1173  // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.

1175  BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1176  ~CachedData();

1178  // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1179  const uint8_t* data;
1180  int length;
1181  bool rejected;
1182  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1183 
1184  private:
1185  // Prevent copying. Not implemented.
1186  CachedData(const CachedData&);
1187  CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&);
1188  };

6712 template <class T>
6713 class Maybe {
6714  public:
6715  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value; }
6716  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value; }
6717 
6718  // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
6719  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
6720  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
6721  return value;
6722  }
6723 
6724  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
6725  return has_value ? value : default_value;
6726  }
6727 
6728  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
6729  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
6730  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
6731  }
6732 
6733  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
6734  return !operator==(other);
6735  }
6736 
6737  private:
6738  Maybe() : has_value(false) {}
6739  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value(true), value(t) {}
6740 
6741  bool has_value;
6742  T value;
6743 
6744  template <class U>
6745  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
6746  template <class U>
6747  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
6748 };
6749

6752 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
6753  return Maybe<T>();
6754 }
6755 
6756 
6757 template <class T>
6758 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
6759  return Maybe<T>(t);

7254 // Tag information for HeapObject.

7259 // Tag information for Smi.
7260 const int kSmiTag = 0;
7261 const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
7262 const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
7263 
7264 template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
7265 
7266 template<int kSmiShiftSize>
7267 V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7268  int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7269  uintptr_t tagged_value =
7270  (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
7271  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
7272 }
7273 
7274 // Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
7275 template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
7276  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
7277  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
7278  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
7279  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
7280  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7281  // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
7282  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
7283  }
7284  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7285  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
7286  }
7287  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7288  // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
7289  // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
7290  // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
7291  // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
7292  //
7293  // CAUTION: The original code below:
7294  // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
7295  // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
7296  // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
7297  // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
7298  // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
7299  return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
7300  }
7301 };
7302 
7303 // Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
7304 template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
7305  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
7306  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
7307  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
7308  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
7309  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7310  // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
7311  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
7312  }
7313  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7314  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
7315  }
7316  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7317  // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
7318  return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
7319  }
7320 };

7325 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
7326 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }

7440  bool value, int shift) {
7441  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
7442  uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);

7494  I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);

8014 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
8015 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8016  typedef internal::Object O;
8017  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
8018  typedef internal::Internals I;
8019  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
8020  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
8021  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
8022  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType) {
8023  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8024  O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
8025  O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
8026  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
8027  }
8028 #endif
8029  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
8030 }
8031 
8032 
8033 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
8034 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8035  typedef internal::Object O;
8036  typedef internal::Internals I;
8037  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
8038  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
8039  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
8040  if (V8_LIKELY(I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType)) {
8041  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8042  return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
8043  }
8044 #endif
8045  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
8046 }

8066 String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {

8069  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
8070  String::ExternalStringResource* result;
8071  if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
8072  void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
8073  result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);

8084 String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
8085  String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
8086  typedef internal::Object O;
8087  typedef internal::Internals I;
8088  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
8089  int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
8090  *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
8091  ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
8092  if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
8093  type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
8094  void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
8095  resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
8096  }
8097 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8098  VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
8099 #endif
8100  return resource;
8101 }

8588 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
8589  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
8590  typedef internal::Internals I;
8591  int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory =
8592  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
8593  I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryOffset);
8594  int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc =
8595  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
8596  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
8597  I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryAtLastGlobalGCOffset);
8598  int64_t amount = *amount_of_external_allocated_memory + change_in_bytes;
8599  if (change_in_bytes > 0 &&
8600  amount - *amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc >
8601  I::kExternalAllocationLimit) {
8602  ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
8603  }
8604  *amount_of_external_allocated_memory = amount;
8605  return *amount_of_external_allocated_memory;
8606 }
